data.description: Don’t miss this rare opportunity to grab a highly upgraded Sun City Festival Jubilee with a south facing, private backyard and solar for energy savings. This gem is loaded! Exterior upgrades include a private Cobblestone courtyard in front and Cobblestone patio in back with water feature & knee wall surrounding the patio extension. The kitchen includes raised panel Maple cabinets, Granite counter-tops, tile backsplash, SS appliances that include the refrigerator, built-in oven & combo convection/microwave, smooth cook-top (but plumbed for gas if you prefer), under-cabinet lighting, large pantry, filtered drinking water at the sink, pull-outs in cabinets, and a breakfast nook with bay window. The pass-through between the dining area & breakfast nook has also been finished with Granite. Other features/upgrades include 3-car garage, tile in all but bedrooms, custom interior paint, wiring for surround sound in great room, fans throughout home, built-in desk/cabinets in utility room for FLEX space, Security system, water softener, hot water recirculating system, built-in storage in both garages, and so much more. The leased solar system has been pre-paid and has 18+ years left on contract. Check under documents tab for a list of the upgrades that cost over $67,000. Many of the features in this home were standard when this home was built. To build a house with these features today it would cost far more than what is represented on this list. Brokered And Advertised By: Ken Meade Realty Listing Agent: Kathy Anderson, GRI, SRES, ePro
